    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The problem with requiring `this` for state variables is that `this` refers to the external interface, where state variables are changed to their getter functions. We could of course twist that since `this` has a special meaning and you could get the external interface using `ContractType(this)`. I don't think anyone is actively using `this.a` for anything else than passing callbacks.",
